19.6.2 Compatibility with HTTP/1.0 Persistent Connections

We need to study this to improve our persistent connection support when
talking to HTTP/1.0-servers.

Check out return code 101 and the Upgrade: header (RFC2616 14.42)

14.39 TE
 The TE request-header field indicates what extension transfer-codings it is
 willing to accept in the response and whether or not it is willing to accept
 trailer fields in a chunked transfer-coding.
